Avril Haines has been selected as the Deputy National Security Advisor by National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice. Haines has previously worked at the State Department, NSC, and Central Intelligence Agency, and has been instrumental in implementing the Administration's strategy to address national security threats. Rice praises Haines' intelligence, dedication to serving the American people, and ability to get things done. She expresses her happiness to have Haines on board to lead the NSC staff and further strengthen American leadership in the world. Rice also thanks Tony Blinken for his service to the NSC and looks forward to continuing to work with him in his new role as Deputy Secretary of State.